<section sectnbr = "3D">
<servcat sctnbr = "03" scnbr = "04">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A3406004" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Propeller Shaft Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A3406002">Propeller Shaft Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A3406004001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Before disassembly propeller shaft, match marks (1) on joint flange (2), viscous coupling (3) and coupling shaft (4) as shown.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect propeller shaft No.1 (5), No.2 (7) and center shaft (6).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A340008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "38.820mm" ver = "01" gw = "197" gh = "94"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A3406004002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A3406005">Coupling Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Reverse disassembly procedure, noting the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When reassembling propeller shaft assembly, align the match marks (1). Otherwise, vibration may occur during driving.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten center coupling nuts and propeller shaft No.2 bolts to specified torque.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T3D003">
<t-part>
Center coupling nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T3D004">
<t-part>
Propeller shaft No.2 bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A340009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.800mm" ver = "01" gw = "198" gh = "116"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
